The Multilateral Convention to Implement Tax Treaty Related Measures to Prevent Base Erosion and Profit Shifting is a multilateral convention of the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development to combat tax avoidance by multinational enterprises (MNEs) through prevention of Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS). The convention was negotiated within the framework of the OECD BEPS project.
The convention was adopted on 24 November 2016, and signed on 24 June 2017 by 70 jurisdictions.
